title: For Sale:  Kimber Ultra CDP .45 1911 Series 1
postcontent:
I'm selling my Kimber Ultra CDP .45 1911. It has served me well and has been replaced by another Kimber. The Ultra CDP is the Kimber Custom Shop 3' 1911. If you're not familiar it is an upgraded Kimber Ultra. It gets extra attention from the Kimber Custom Shop. Here is the info for the series II pistol. http://www.kimberamerica.com/1911/cdp-ii/ultra-cdp-ii As listed above mine is a series 1, which are becoming harder to find. 

The pistol has some holster wear from being carried daily (see pictures). The gun works flawlessly and has been a true nail driver for everyone that fires it from myself to my 12 year old son. 

Included with the gun is the original box, papers, lock and Kimber magazine. In addition I'm including one black and two stainless Chip McCormick Magazines (the Kimber and black CM magazines just had the springs replaced with new Wolff springs last month and the two stainless CM magazine are less than a month old). I'm also including a brand new unopened Wolff recoil spring pack. 

New these go for over $1200 plus tax or shipping and transfer. Like I mentioned the series 1 are harder to find so my listed price of $950 for everything I'm including is more than fair. I've probably fired around 1000 flawless rounds through this gun and every round has been quality, all brass cased rounds from major manufactures. The round count is probably high but I want to be as accurate as possible.  If you're considering a 1911 or a Kimber this is your chance to get a high quality one for a lot less than new. 

Not really looking for trades but I also believe in never saying never so if you ask about a trade please let me know what you have and what kind of deal you're thinking. CCW preferred for sale but at a minimum you must be 21 with a valid AZ drivers license. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Akdal MKA-1919
postcontent:
Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun by Akdal Arms. This weapon is intended for civilian and security use, and mimics the famous M16 rifle in its layout and placement of most controls. It is remarkably light for its caliber and size, because of extensive use of modern, high strength plastics.

Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun utilizes conventional gas-operated action with annual (ring-type) gas piston, which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel. Return spring is also located around the same tube, which is concealed by enlarged polymer handguards. Barrel is quick-removable from upper receiver, barrel locking is achieved by tilting locking piece inside the bolt, which engages the barrel extension. Charging handle is attached to the bolt and projects on the right side of the receiver. The upper receiver is manufactured from aluminum alloy; lower receiver, along with pistol grip and shoulder stock, is manufactured as one piece from impact-resistant polymer. Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun utilizes detachable box magazines, each holding 5 rounds; an M16-style bolt stop and bolt release button are incorporated into the lower receiver. Manual safety also duplicates M16-style, being located on the left side of the receiver, above the pistol grip. Standard sights include front post, installed on the M16-style removable base, and a detachable M16A2-style carrying handle with built-in diopter sight.
